snippet.title: Basis Science Basis B1 Band
snippet.description: The $199 Basis Band offers a powerful mix of sensors and motivational tools, but pass if you'd rather spend less on a fitness tracker or aren't partial to big, watch-style designs.

snippet.title: Food Cycle Science Food Cycler: Home
snippet.description: This luxurious in-home composter promises to recycle your food waste in a matter of hours.

snippet.title: Brinkster Web Host
snippet.description: Brinkster offers a reasonable amount of bandwidth and storage for a low price, but its above-average technical support makes it stand out.

snippet.title: AOL Reader (Web app)
snippet.description: The new AOL Reader has many of the same features found in other popular RSS newsreaders. It looks like one of a few good alternatives for those losing Google Reader next week.

snippet.title: 'New Kind of Science' falls short of its iPad e-book potential
snippet.description: New support for Retina graphics helps a lot, but Stephen Wolfram's magnum opus about math, computing, and physics could be so much more.

snippet.title: Museum of Science Fiction might be coming to DC
snippet.description: Trekkies and wanna-be Mars colonists might soon have a permanent brick-and-mortar site for sharing their love of all things science fiction.

snippet.title: Shutdown will largely shutter NASA, other science projects
snippet.description: Furloughs are expected to impact several federal science programs, but essential services related to nation's safety and defense will be unaffected.
